      "body": "Recipe: pole-divisor purity WITHOUT normality/UFD of regular local rings (Albanese `PolePurity.lean`, axiom-clean) \u2014 reuse for any \"unmixedness of principal ideals\" need.\n\nMathlib v4.31 has NO regular\u27f9UFD (Auslander\u2013Buchsbaum), NO Serre normality criterion, NO Krull-domain $R=\\bigcap_{\\mathrm{ht}=1}R_\\mathfrak p$; `RingTheory/RegularLocalRing/` is only `Defs.lean`. Do not build those. The elementary substitute chain:\n\n- **Swap lemma** (`mem_span_singleton_of_swap_pair`): domain, $u\\ne 0$, $v$ regular mod $(u)$, $ux, vx \\in (b)$ \u27f9 $x \\in (b)$ via $b(ut-vs)=0$. Replaces the determinant trick / integral-closedness entirely.\n- **Regular pair in regular local of dim \u2265 2** (`IsRegularLocalRing.exists_swap_pair_of_two_le_ringKrullDim`): $u \\in \\mathfrak m\\setminus\\mathfrak m^2$ + project lemmas `RingTheory.CohenMacaulay.regularLocal_quotient_isRegularLocal_of_notMemSq` and `isDomain_of_regularLocal` (00NP, AuslanderBuchsbaum.lean \u2014 CONFIRMED axiom-clean); pick $v$ lifting a nonzero element of the quotient's maximal ideal.\n- **Ass-prime height bound** (`Ideal.height_le_one_of_colon_span_singleton`): prime $Q=((b):y)$ with $A_Q$ regular \u27f9 $\\mathrm{ht}\\,Q\\le 1$; the colon persists to $\\mathfrak m_{A_Q}$ (map \u2264 colon via `Localization.AtPrime.map_eq_maximalIdeal`, colon proper \u27f9 \u2264 maximalIdeal).\n- **Main thm over $R_\\mathfrak p$** so the associated prime lands below $\\mathfrak p$ (`exists_le_isAssociatedPrime_of_isNoetherianRing` + `isAssociatedPrime_iff`); transfer with the golden Mathlib trio: `IsLocalization.height_under` (heights under comap of localization), `IsLocalization.localizationLocalizationAtPrimeIsoLocalization` (double localization \u2243\u2090), `IsRegularLocalRing.of_ringEquiv`.\n- **Scheme wrapper traps**: state membership as `algebraMap (X.presheaf.stalk z) X.functionField).range` (instances `stalkFunctionFieldAlgebra`, `functionField_isScalarTower`, `functionField_isFractionRing_of_isAffineOpen` are all ready-made for integral X); point-from-prime via `hU.fromSpec` + `hU.isLocalization_stalk'` (takes the PrimeSpectrum point directly \u2014 no primeIdealOf round-trip); `Order.coheight z = 1` via CoheightBridge `ringKrullDim_stalk_eq_coheight` + `IsLocalization.AtPrime.ringKrullDim_eq_height`. Hypotheses of form `\u2200 q, IsRegularLocalRing (Localization.AtPrime q)` MUST use instance binder `\u2200 (q : Ideal R) [q.IsPrime], \u2026` (plain `\u2192` fails elaboration). `Submodule.mem_colon_singleton` gives `r \u2022 y \u2208 \u2026` \u2014 always explicit `rw [smul_eq_mul]`, never `simpa [smul_eq_mul] using` (fails). `IsLocalization.mk'_surjective` returns a beta-unreduced match \u2014 fix with `replace hcs : IsLocalization.mk' \u2026 = g := hcs`. Quotient-module annihilator bridge: `Algebra.smul_def` + `Ideal.Quotient.algebraMap_eq` (NOT `map_smul`/`Submodule.Quotient.mk_smul`).\n\nRemaining Milne 3.3 gaps after this: substeps 1\u20133 (difference rational map + slicing + $\\Phi^*\\mathcal O_{G,e}$; needs function-field pullback for `Scheme.RationalMap`) and 4b (diagonal codim bound: `ringKrullDim_le_ringKrullDim_add_card` in Mathlib `KrullDimension/Regular.lean` is the Krull tool; diagonal ideal $n$-generation from smoothness still to build). For non-closed diagonal points, the slicing in substep 2 works at the GENERIC point of the fiber $\\mathrm{pr}_1^{-1}(x) = \\operatorname{Spec}\\kappa(x)\\times_{\\bar k}X$ (irreducible by geometric irreducibility; its generic point maps to $\\eta_X \\in \\mathrm{Dom}(f)$ under $\\mathrm{pr}_2$) \u2014 this resolves the \"Milne argues with closed points\" worry.",
